properties.notes: The north boundary runs along Garlic Mountain, Spanish Mountain and Obelisk to the Middle fork of the Kings River. The east boundary is the Middle Fork of the Kings River. The south boundary is the Kings River. The west boundary is just East of Fox Canyon and East of Rogers Ridge. This zone is roughly 4.5 miles from north to south and 10 miles wide.

South boundary includes the areas both north and south of McKinley Grove Road, and runs south of Dinkey Mountain.  The boundary runs north to include Dinkey Creek, and runs about a half mile north of Dinkey Creek Campground.  The boundary continues to the east, west of Nelson Mountain.  This zone is roughly 4.25 miles from north to south and 4 miles wide.

South boundary lays north of Sycamore Springs Road.  West boundary its at the intersection of Ross Crossing Road and Trimmer Springs Road.  The west boundary continues north to contain Nutmeg Glen along Ross Crossing Road. The north boundary ends south of Dinkey Mountain.  The east boundary ends a half of a mile east of Ross Crossing Campground.  This zone is roughly 6.45 miles from north to south and 10 miles wide.

South Boundary is just north of the Dinkey-Trimmer Road and Ross Crossing Road intersection.  West Boundary is a half a mile west of the Big Creek Road and Vomac Clovis Drive intersection.  The north boundary is a mile north of the Nutmeg Campground (Off of Big Creek Road).  East boundary contains Dinkey Trimmer Road. This zone is roughly 5.5 miles from north to south and 2.8 miles wide.

The north boundary is about one quarter mile south of North Fork Kings River. The east boundary is the Kings Canyon National Forest. and Inyo County. The south boundary is Obelisk and Spanish Mountain. The west boundary is west of Hoffman Mountain. This zone is roughly 9 miles from north to south and 9 miles wide.

West boundary begins at the intersection of Blackrock Road and Vomac Road.  The north boundary runs a quarter of a mile north of the intersection of McKinley Grove Road and Blackrock Road.  The east border runs east of Granite Gorge in the north, and runs east of Rodgers Ridge at the end of Vomac Way.  This zone is roughly 7 miles from north to south and 11 miles wide.

The south boundary lays north of Kirch Flat Campground.  The west boundary is at the intersection of Trimmer Springs Road and Ross Crossing Road.  The north boundary contains the areas north of Trimmer Springs Road and Sycamore Springs Road.  The east boundary is at the end of Vomac Road. This zone is roughly 3.5 miles from north to south and 4 miles wide.

South boundary lays north of Sawmill Flat and south of Sugarpine Hill.  The west boundary is a quarter of a mile from the Ross Crossing Road and McKinley Grove Road intersection.  The north boundary extends (includes) property north of Courtright Reservoir.  The east boundary ends east of (including) Wishon Reservoir. This zone is roughly 15 miles from north to south and 12 miles wide.

Contains both sides of Dinkey Creek Road (including) just west of Blue Canyon Vista Observation.  It follows Dinkey Creek Road to the east until just outside Summit Meadow Campground.  The north boundary is south (excluding) of the shoreline of Shaver Lake and Fishing Club.  This zone is roughly 4.25 miles from north to south and 4 miles wide.

Contains both sides of Bretz Mill Road, just east of it's intersection of Cressmans Road.  The south boundary contains properties on Providence Creek Road, to it's intersection with Big Creek.  The north boundary extends to include the properties off of Bretz Mill Road from Providence Creek Road. This zone is roughly 2.6 miles from north to south and 4 miles wide.

The south and west boundary lays just north of Dinkey Creek.   The west boundary continues north to contain both sides of Rock Creek Road until just south of the "Brewer Lake Trail Turnoff".  The north boundary is just north of Foster Ridge as well as the Dinkey Lakes Trailhead.  This zone is roughly 3.8 miles from north to south and 5.4 miles wide.
